Package: framedf
Type: Package
Title: First-Pass Triage of Unfamiliar Data Frames
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Gilles", "Colling", email = "gilles.colling051@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3070-6066"))
Description: A first-pass diagnostic for data frames. Infers a semantic
    role for each column (identifier, temporal, spatial, categorical,
    continuous, compositional), screens all sensible pairs of columns for
    meaningful, suspicious, and structural relationships, and surfaces a
    small set of anomalies (implausible ranges, distributional outliers,
    inconsistent capitalisation, totals exceeding bounds). Output is
    qualitative: direction, strength, and stability, expressed as
    sentences. Built for the first thirty seconds of working with an
    unfamiliar dataset, and scaled to millions of rows through
    progressive subsampling.
